title: Sardar Ali wins PP-2 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Sardar Muhammad Ali Khan an independent candidate has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-2 Attock II by securing 36,093 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Iftikhar Ahmed Khan of PML-N who bagged 35,891 votes.
The votersâ€™ turnout remained 57.74 per cent.
